# Unified Ambulance Emergency System — Complete Agent Prompt (v2)

> This is the single source of truth for all three surfaces: Client App, Admin Dashboard, and Driver App.
> All developers, agents, and code generators must follow this specification exactly.

---

## System Overview

An Ambulance Emergency Booking System with three interconnected surfaces:

| Surface | Users | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Client App | Patients (public) | Request ambulances, choose company, track in real-time |
| Admin Dashboard | Company Admins / Super Admins | Monitor drivers, view completed trips, manage ambulances, evaluate performance |
| Driver App | Registered drivers only | Receive requests directly, accept/deny, navigate to patient, notify on completion |

All three surfaces share a **single backend**, a **single database**, and communicate via **REST APIs + Socket.io real-time events**.

**Database:** SQLite3 (development) → PostgreSQL or MySQL (production)
**Maps:** React-Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (no API key required — used across all surfaces)
**Real-time:** Socket.io (primary), Firebase (optional fallback for location streams)

---

## Core Dispatch Philosophy

> **Requests go DIRECTLY to the driver. The admin does NOT sit in the approval chain.**

- The patient selects an ambulance → the request is sent **directly to the assigned driver**.
- The driver **accepts or denies** the booking — no admin approval gate.
- The admin **monitors only**: they see all incoming bookings, driver responses, active trips, and completed orders in real-time — but they do not block or approve the flow.
- After a trip is completed, the driver notifies the system (`trip_completed`), which the admin sees on their dashboard.
- Admin uses the dashboard to **evaluate driver performance**: how many orders taken, how much earned, response rates, ratings, etc.

