## 6. Real-Time Socket.io Event Map

All three surfaces join a booking room: `room:booking_{bookingId}`

| Event | Emitter | Listeners | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `join_driver_room` | Driver App | Server | Driver joins private room `driver_room_{driverId}` on connect/reconnect |
| `new_booking` | Client App | **Driver** (primary), Admin (monitor only) | Patient submits booking — sent directly to driver |
| `driver_accepted` | Driver App | Client, Admin (monitor) | Driver accepts trip — client proceeds to tracking |
| `driver_denied` | Driver App | Admin (monitor/fallback) | Driver denies — admin notified for optional reassignment |
| `driver_location_update` | Driver App | Client, Admin | GPS every 5 seconds |
| `patient_location_update` | Client App | Driver, Admin | GPS every 5 seconds |
| `trip_completed` | Driver App | Client, Admin | Trip ended — client shows rating page, admin records completion |
| `payment_confirmed` | Admin | Client | Payment confirmed |

> **Note:** `booking_accepted` and `ambulance_dispatched` events from admin are removed from the primary flow. Admin no longer dispatches. The driver's `driver_accepted` event is the trigger that moves the booking forward.

