## 10. Key Design Rules

1. **One login page, smart routing** — role detected server-side, redirect client-side
2. **Admins use email + password** — drivers use name + driver ID
3. **Drivers created by admin only** — no self-serve driver registration
4. **Requests go directly to the driver** — no admin approval gate in the normal flow
5. **Admin monitors, not dispatches** — admin sees everything in real-time but does not block the booking flow
6. **Driver notifies on completion** — `trip_completed` is emitted by the driver, admin sees it on the dashboard
7. **Admin evaluates driver performance** — orders taken, orders denied, earnings, ratings, response time
8. **Admin fallback only** — admin can manually reassign only if a driver denies or times out
9. **Each company's units show separately on client** — patients see and choose by company
10. **Dispatch always shows real names** — Company Name + Driver Name + Driver ID + call buttons
11. **Driver app is SafeBoda-style** — full-screen incoming request sent directly, accept/deny with timeout
12. **Everything syncs** — all booking state changes propagate instantly to all three surfaces via Socket.io rooms
13. **Single database** — client app, admin, and driver app all read/write the same tables
14. **Maps everywhere use Leaflet + OpenStreetMap** — no Google Maps, no API key required
15. **Coordinate Safety** — Every map marker must validate that Latitude and Longitude are valid numbers before rendering
16. **Socket Resilience** — All clients must rejoin their specific rooms immediately upon socket reconnection
17. **Client Persistence** — Ongoing bookings must survive browser refreshes/restarts using storage persistence